<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I've been soloing the aquaduct tanglers for the last few levels and its been the fastest xp yet, specially with serenity to decrease downtime.<BR>Try this before you start a fight, pull them once and run but keep a eye on them, you will notice that they stop and turn around at a certain spot.  Park your telamon about 10 feet after that spot and go pull them again, run to your parked telamon and wait.  When they turn around again and start walking back AE root them.  Then mez any that didnt get caught in the root and kill them first with telamon and a nuke or two all while keeping an eye on the rooted group incase they come out of root before you excpect it.  After you finsh the mezed, mez the rooted group and kill them also.  This is very dangerous and you will die a few times but I'm getting about .1 - .15 per pull (around 300-350m xp a pull) from the aquaduct.  Plus I use my realm DoT whenever its available by sending the pet in to draw agro, hit dot when they are around it and run like hell.  Its like a free pull basically that doestn cost you any power      <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><BR>Note that the tanglers will nearly always turn around in the exact same spot to head back, just dont attack them before they turn around or else it will be very tough to CC them before they start pounding on you.  You could probably do this w/o AE root but I have found that its the best way to increase CC time so I can kill them all 1v1<BR>Good luck and I would not try doing this till your at least L45.  And do this from the side fodzer says to also, dont have to worry about other people and its alot flater with more room to work.
</FONT>
